==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From French ''[[passeport]]'', from ''[[passer]]'' ‘pass’ + ''[[port#French|port]]'' ‘port’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈpɑ:spɔ:t/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[official]] [[document]] which proves the [[identity]] and [[nationality]] of the person for whom it was [[issue]]d.
#:''You will have to bring your '''passport''' to prove who you are.''

